 Input
Four non negative integers. 
The first input is an integer representing the number of 100 rupee notes.
The second input is an integer representing the number of 10 rupee notes.
The third input is an integer representing the number of 1 rupee notes.
The fourth input is an integer representing the price of the item.

Output
You have to output 1 if the item is affordable.
You have to output 0 if the item is not affordable.


#include <stdio.h>
int main() 
{
int x,y,z,n,sum;
/*printf("The first input is an integer representing the number of 100 rupee notes.\n");*/
scanf("%d",&x);
/*printf("The first input is an integer representing the number of 10 rupee notes\n.");*/
scanf("%d",&y);
/*printf("The first input is an integer representing the number of 1 rupee notes\n.");*/
scanf("%d",&z);
/*printf("The fourth input is an integer representing the price of the item\n.");*/
scanf("%d",&n);
sum=100*x+10*y+1*z;
if (sum>=n)
printf("1");
else
printf("0");
}

